definitions.definition: An inexpensive, disposable box -like container fashioned from either paper , paper with wax-covering ( wax paper ), or other lightweight material.
examples: a carton of milk or eggs

definitions.definition: A pack of cigarettes , usually ten, wrapped in cellophane or packed in a light cardboard box .
A cardboard box that holds (usually 24) beer bottles or cans .
A small disc within the bullseye of a target.
A shot that strikes this disc.
